name: IBIF v2 - land occupation - biodiversity intactness - vertebrates
description: Intactness-based Biodiversity Impact Factors (IBIF) for land occupation impacts on terrestrial biodiversity intactness, (vertebrates). Includes all land use types: cropland, pasture, plantation forest, urban land, and mines. Based on GLOBIO 4 model and Mean Species Abundance (MSA) metric. Original units MSA·km2/km2 converted to MSA·km2/m2 to match ecoinvent land occupation flows (m2·yr). From Schipper et al. 2025: https://doi.org/10.1038/s41597-025-05946-1. Country-level entries include a GDP-based weight used to compute weighted averages when aggregating to composite or unspecified regions.
